;; MELPA Recipe for doing.el
;;
;; This file contains the recipe to submit to MELPA.
;;
;; Submission Instructions:
;; ------------------------
;;
;; 1. Fork https://github.com/melpa/melpa
;;
;; 2. Create a new file at recipes/doing with this content:
;;
;;    (doing :repo "xiaoxinghu/doing.el" :fetcher github)
;;
;; 3. Test the recipe locally:
;;    cd melpa
;;    make recipes/doing
;;    make sandbox INSTALL=doing
;;
;; 4. Create a pull request with commit message:
;;    Add recipe for doing.el
;;
;;    doing.el is an Org-mode based activity log for frictionless time
;;    tracking and reporting, inspired by Brett Terpstra's doing CLI tool.
;;
;; 5. Wait for MELPA maintainers to review (typically 1-4 weeks)
;;
;; 6. Address any feedback and update the PR as needed
;;
;; 7. Once merged, the package will be available on MELPA within 24 hours
;;
;; For MELPA Stable:
;; -----------------
;; MELPA Stable builds from git tags. To release on MELPA Stable:
;;
;; 1. Tag a release: git tag -a v0.1.0 -m "Release 0.1.0"
;; 2. Push the tag: git push origin v0.1.0
;; 3. MELPA Stable will automatically pick up tagged releases
;;
;; The same recipe works for both MELPA and MELPA Stable.
;;
;; References:
;; -----------
;; - MELPA Contributing: https://github.com/melpa/melpa/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.org
;; - Recipe Format: https://github.com/melpa/melpa#recipe-format
